Wireshark Notes - Madni 

> FILTER FOR PROTOCOLS: You can just write down the protocol name in the search bar. You can enter the following protocol names to search them.
- DNS  - HTTP - FTP - SSH - ARP - TELNET - ICMP

> FILTER FOR IP ADDRESS: By entering this command, we can find details about specific IP addresses.
- ip.addr == 0.0.0.0 (Example ip address)
- ip.src == 0.0.0.0 (It will list the Source IP address given in the argument.)
- ip.dst == 0.0.0.0 (It will find out destination packet going to 0.0.0.0)

> FILTER BY MAC ADDRESS: 
- eth.addr == 01:23:45:67:89:AB (It will filter out all logs related to 01:23:45:67:89:AB)

> FILTER BY PORT NUMBER:
- udp.port == 53
- tcp.port == 25
